chunk_content: Collection of expanded age data is needed for planning appropriate HIV services for older adults as well as integrated service needs. As the treatment cohort continues to age, the ability to monitor lifelong patient outcomes is critical. In FY 2022, the TX_CURR 50+ age band was expanded to 50-54, 55-59, 60-64, 65+. In FY 2023, these age bands were expanded for all treatment and viral suppression indicators. There will be a 50+ age band option for circumstances where reporting on 50-54, 55-59, 60-64, 65+ is not feasible. Please note, while age-bands were collapsed for target setting in COP23 (FY24), five-year age bands will still be required for reporting results. The simplified age bands will be available for comparing results to targets in Panorama for FY 24. GHSD-PEPFAR will continue to monitor implementation and trends by the five-year age bands and expects others within PEPFAR to do the same.
